---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International DJs | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for DJs working internationally, covering DJ careers abroad, touring positions, and global nightlife and festival opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International DJs";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for DJs working abroad, performing internationally, and pursuing careers across clubs, festivals, and entertainment venues worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/dj-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/dj-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International DJ Careers</h2>
      <p>
        DJs curate and mix music to create experiences for audiences across clubs, festivals, and events. International DJ careers offer opportunities to perform worldwide, build global audiences, and participate in the international dance music and nightlife industries.
      </p>
      <p>
        International DJ opportunities exist through touring circuits, festival appearances worldwide, residencies in international clubs, and the inherently global nature of electronic music culture and nightlife entertainment.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for DJs working abroad across clubs, festivals, and entertainment venues worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for DJs</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Self-arranged typically' },
          { need: 'Hearing coverage', why: 'Essential professional tool', typical: 'Critical for profession' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Touring demands', typical: 'Essential for career' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Lifestyle and career pressure', typical: 'Consider including' },
          { need: 'Equipment coverage', why: 'Professional gear', typical: 'Separate policy' },
          { need: 'Irregular hours', why: 'Nightlife schedule', typical: 'Consider health impacts' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Hearing Protection</h3>
      <p>
        DJs work in extremely loud environments night after night. Prolonged exposure to high volume levels creates serious hearing damage risk. Hearing is essential to the profession—protecting it through prevention and coverage is critical.
      </p>
      <p>
        Tinnitus and hearing loss are occupational hazards for DJs. Coverage for hearing healthcare, preventive care, and potential hearing-related conditions is among the most important considerations for DJ health coverage.
      </p>

      <h3>Touring Lifestyle</h3>
      <p>
        International DJing involves constant travel—flights, time zones, hotels, and varying conditions. The touring lifestyle creates unique health demands. Coverage that works across countries and supports continuous travel is essential for touring DJs.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Club DJ</h3>
      <p>
        Nightclub performances. Self-arranged coverage typically. Venue-based. Clubs offer consistency.
      </p>

      <h3>Festival DJ</h3>
      <p>
        Festival circuit appearances. Self-arranged coverage. Seasonal peaks. Festivals offer scale.
      </p>

      <h3>Touring DJ</h3>
      <p>
        International touring. Self-arranged essential. Continuous travel. Touring offers reach.
      </p>

      <h3>Resident DJ</h3>
      <p>
        Club residency positions. Possible venue benefits. Regular schedule. Residency offers stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Radio/Online</h3>
      <p>
        Broadcast and streaming. Platform benefits possible. Studio-based. Broadcasting offers audience.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for DJs"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for DJs working abroad across clubs, festivals, and entertainment venues worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare DJ Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>DJ Skills</h3>
      <p>
        Mixing ability. Music selection. Crowd reading. Skills demonstrated through performance.
      </p>

      <h3>Production</h3>
      <p>
        Original music production. Release catalog. Chart success. Production elevates profile.
      </p>

      <h3>Following</h3>
      <p>
        Audience building. Social media presence. Stream numbers. Following enables booking.
      </p>

      <h3>Reputation</h3>
      <p>
        Industry standing. Club relationships. Festival connections. Reputation drives career.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Hearing</h3>
      <p>
        Extreme sound exposure. Nightly high volumes. Cumulative damage risk. Hearing coverage critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Schedule</h3>
      <p>
        Night work standard. Sleep disruption. Circadian challenges. Schedule impacts health.
      </p>

      <h3>Travel</h3>
      <p>
        Constant movement. Time zone changes. Travel fatigue. Comprehensive travel coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Lifestyle Pressure</h3>
      <p>
        Party environment. Social expectations. Career uncertainty. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Performance</h3>
      <p>
        Live DJ sets. Crowd engagement. Energy management. Performance delivers experience.
      </p>

      <h3>Music Preparation</h3>
      <p>
        Track selection. Set planning. Music discovery. Preparation enables performance.
      </p>

      <h3>Business</h3>
      <p>
        Booking management. Promotion. Branding. Business sustains career.
      </p>

      <h3>Production</h3>
      <p>
        Original music creation. Remix work. Release management. Production builds catalog.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Circuit</h3>
      <p>
        DJ careers inherently international. Global clubs and festivals. Travel constant. Industry truly worldwide.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Local to touring DJ. Festival headliner. Producer-DJ. Label owner. Multiple paths.
      </p>

      <h3>Income Variability</h3>
      <p>
        Booking-dependent income. Seasonal patterns. Competition intense. Financial planning important.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Longevity</h3>
      <p>
        Physical demands of touring. Lifestyle sustainability. Hearing preservation critical. Longevity requires intention.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a DJ considering international touring. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Hearing coverage critical. Travel coverage essential. Self-arranged coverage typical. Career demands significant health attention.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do clubs or booking agencies provide coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Rarely for performers. Some residencies may include. Touring typically doesn't. Self-arranged coverage standard.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">How important is hearing coverage for DJs?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Absolutely critical. Sound exposure extreme. Career depends on hearing. Prioritize hearing protection and coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about the touring lifestyle and health?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Demanding on health. Sleep disruption common. Travel stress real. Comprehensive coverage and self-care essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Should I have equipment coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes if owning gear. Separate from health coverage. Essential for touring. Equipment valuable to protect.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Electronic music global. Competition intense. Quality and marketing matter. Outlook varies by positioning.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by prioritizing hearing coverage as critical career protection. Ensure comprehensive travel coverage for touring demands. Consider mental health support for lifestyle pressures. Arrange equipment coverage separately for professional gear.
      </p>
      <p>
        DJs create unforgettable experiences worldwide. Your coverage should support performance careers—protecting your hearing, covering travel demands, and maintaining your health across DJ engagements worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your DJ Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for DJs working abroad across clubs, festivals, and entertainment venues worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
